#If-Else Basic
1)Write a program to check if a number is positive or negative
n=int(input("enter the number:"))
if n >0:
    print("positive integer")
else:
    print("negative integer")


2)Check if a number is even or odd:
n=int(input("enter the number:"))
if n%2==0:
    print("even number")
else:
    print("odd number")



3)Determine if a person is eligible to vote (age >= 18):
age=int(input("enter the age:"))
if age>=18:
    print("you are eligible for vote")
else:
    print("you are not eligible for vote")




4)Check if a given number is zero, positive, or negative:
n=int(input("enter the number"))
if n>0:
    print("positive number")
elif n==0:
    print("zero")
else:
    print("negative number")



5)Determine if a number is a multiple of 3:
s=int(input("enter the number"))
if s%3==0:
    print("divisible by 3")
else:
    print("not div by 3")



6)Take a number as input and print "Yes" if it is greater than 10, else print "No":
s=int(input("enter the number"))
if s>10:
    print("yes")
else:
    print("No")



7)Check if a character is a vowel or a consonant:
s=input("enter the letter:")
if s=="a" or s=="e" or s=="i" or s=="o" or s=="u":
    print("vowel")
else:
    print("consonant")



8)Determine if a number is a single-digit number:
a=int(input("enter the digit"))
if abs(a>0) and abs(a<=9):
    print("single digit")
else:
    print("not a single digit")



9)Find the greatest of two numbers:
n=int(input("enter 1st number:"))
m=int(input("enter 2nd number:"))
if n>m:
    print("1st number is greater")
else:
    print("2nd number is greater")



10)Check if a given number is divisible by both 5 and 11:
a=int(input("enter the number"))
if a%5==0 and a%11==0:
    print("divisible by both 5 and 11")
else:
    print("Not divisible")



11)Check if a character is an uppercase or lowercase letter:
s=input("enter the character:")
if s.isupper():
    print("upper case")
else:
    print("lower case")



12)Check if a number is within the range of 1 to 100:
n=int(input("enter the number:"))
if n in range(1, 100):
    print("Yes, it is from 1 to 100")
else:
    print("No, it is not from 1 to 100")



13)Write a program to determine if a given year is a leap year:
a=int(input("enter the number:"))
if a%4==0:
    print("this is a leap year")
else:
    print("this is not a leap year") 


    
14)Check whether a triangle is valid based on its three sides:
m=int(input("enter 1st number"))
n=int(input("enter 2nd number"))
o=int(input("enter 3rd number"))
if (m+n<=o)or(m+o<=n)or(n+o<=m): 
    print("triangle is valid")
else:
    print("triangle is not valid")





15)Given the length and breadth of a rectangle, determine if it is a square:
l=int(input("enter the length"))
b=int(input("enter the breadth"))
if l==b:
    print("Square")
else:
    print("Not a Square")












    





